(10, 'Dolly Parton shocks fans by breaking one of her oldest rules - and it\'s met with calls for her to run for President', '\r\n36\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nJack Slater\r\nSat, May 20, 2023 at 4:57 PM GMT+2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDolly Parton has spoken out about politics, breaking her own rule\r\n\r\nDolly Parton is never one to play by the rule book &ndash; not even her own, if her latest interview is anything to go by.\r\nDolly, who is swapping her country roots for&nbsp;a full-on rock album this year, might be inspired by the rebellious nature of the genre as she speaks out on politicians in a new interview.\r\nQuoting the lyrics of her new single, World on Fire, back to her, a host on The Today Show read Dolly&rsquo;s surprisingly fiery takedown of politicians.\r\n&ldquo;Don\'t get me started on politics, Now how are we to live in a world like this, Greedy politicians, present and past, They wouldn\'t know the truth if it bit \'em in the ass.&rdquo;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDolly Parton might be feeling more rebellious as she gears up to release her first rock album\r\n\r\nThese are the words read back to Dolly, who laughs as a response. She&rsquo;s then asked which politicians she&rsquo;s talking about.\r\n\r\n- ADVERTISEMENT -\r\n\r\n\r\n&ldquo;All of them. any of them.&rdquo; She replies, plainly.\r\nShe then adds, &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t think any of them are trying hard enough&hellip; They worry more about their party than they do about the people.&rdquo;\r\nDolly added the better approach would be &ldquo;If we just do what we felt was the right thing rather than who&rsquo;s going to lose or who&rsquo;s going to win this, or who&rsquo;s going to look better if they do this.&rdquo;\r\nIt&rsquo;s a bold departure from Dolly&rsquo;s usual approach to talking politics &ndash; but people on social media have reacted positively to the normally reserved superstar speaking out.\r\nMany fans said the same thing, writing &ldquo;Dolly for president&rdquo; while another pointed out that Dolly has never forgotten where she came from, always putting the needs of the people before anything else.\r\nDespite being well-known for her huge heart,&nbsp;charitable endeavours, and not being afraid to wade in and help those in need, she&rsquo;s famously shied away from really talking about how she aligns.\r\nIn fact, after appearing at the Emmy Awards in 2017 with her 9 to 5 co-stars Jane Fonda and Lily Tomlin, Dolly shared the rule she tends to live by when it comes to speaking politics.\r\nAt the awards show, Jane and Lily went a little bit off script, lashing out at then President Donald Trump.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDolly Parton used to avoid talking politics - even after her 9 to 5 costars lashed out at Trump live onstage\r\n\r\nNot long after, Dolly told&nbsp;The Guardian, &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t like to be known by the company I keep, so to speak. I want to be my own individual self. If I&rsquo;ve got something to say, I&rsquo;ll say it, but I don&rsquo;t want to be dragged into it.&rdquo;\r\nShe added about the event with Jane and Lily, &ldquo;I just did not want everybody to think that whatever they think is what I think. I don&rsquo;t really like getting up on TV and saying political things. I don&rsquo;t even want to make a deal out of it, but I want people to know I&rsquo;m my own individual self.&rdquo;\r\nAs for her own political views, she knows what they are and that&rsquo;s good enough for her. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve got as many Republican friends as I&rsquo;ve got Democrat friends and I just don&rsquo;t like voicing my opinion on things,&rdquo; she says.\r\n&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve seen things before, like the Dixie Chicks. You can ruin a career for speaking out. I respect my audience too much for that, I respect myself too much for that. Of course, I have my own opinions, but that don&rsquo;t mean I got to throw them out there because you&rsquo;re going to p*ss off half the people.&rdquo;\r\n\r\n', 'dolly-parton-shocks-fans-by-breaking-one-of-her-oldest-rules---and-it\'s-met-with-calls-for-her-to-run-for-president', 'http://localhost/sylvain/public/uploads/hesed-sarl8631ba03be283907e8d87355eb0d575b6469768807434.jpg', 'https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/dolly-parton-shocks-fans-breaking-145738527.html', '1', 'jison nongolola', '2023-05-21 04:08:25', '2023-05-21 10:27:24'),
